{
  "texts": [
    "Self-curation methods have been proposed to improve the alignment of judges.",
    "Yuan et al. (2024) introduced self-rewarding LMs that generate both responses and reward signals to create preference datasets for direct preference optimization (DPO) (Rafailov et al., 2023).",
    "Pang et al. (2024) and Trivedi et al. (2024) explored rationalization-based preferences by generating multiple CoT explanations from a fixed seed model.",
    "Other works (Xu et al., 2023; Zhang et al., 2023) integrated iterative feedback from stronger models or humans to refine evaluation granularity.",
    "While these methods improve alignment, they often rely on aggressive fine-tuning, which can introduce variance and bias."
  ]
}